description:
Our place is close to Pratt Institute and Fort Greene Park. You’ll love our place because of the neighborhood, the kitchen, the comfy beds, the outdoors space, and the light. Our place is good for couples,  business travelers, and families (with kids).

Beautiful duplex in a brownstone located in the heart of Brooklyn. Close to transportation, restaurants, Fort Green park and 30 min to the city

Guest can access the whole duplex and the back yard

We are not going to be there but can be reached through text, email or a phone call at anytime

photos.caption: Dining room. Connected to the kitchen
Beautiful Brownstone with an open kitchen to a dining area.
Original crown moulding Make this historic brownstone so special. Just lay on the couch and stair at the ceiling
Renovated kitchen with a chef stove and a dish washer. We have tons of herbs, coffee and much more for you to use
Powder room on the parlor floor
The owners are designer so you will find great items scattered around the house
Ground floor bedroom - Queen size bed with adjusted bathroom and a backyard access
Ground floor full bath with a claw foot tub and a huge shower head
2nd bedroom with 2 twin size beds. This is the kids room and we have Lego, books, building blocks and much more for you to use.
Kids bedroom's mantel with an old Centre Pompidou poster
Office on the ground floor with 3 desks for you to use
Back yard - access through the ground floor
Our chicken. They are in the coop when Airbnb guests are in. In the Spring and summer you can enjoy fresh eggs

review.comments: My family had a marvelous time staying at Shay & Anat's beautifully decorated and spacious home.  It was like living in a lifestyle magazine but we were never worried that our kids would damage anything -- it's not precious.  The subway station is really close.  There are good restaurants nearby.  The kitchen is well equipped with everything from a standing mixer to a sausage maker!
